{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place milk into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>2 min\/105°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.  ","Add flour, yeast, salt, and sugar and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Let rest in mixing bowl 10 minutes. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl and set aside. ","Add water and baking soda and knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer to prepared bowl and let rest 30 minutes. ","Lightly grease a frying pan and set over a low to medium heat. Grease the inside of egg rings and arrange in frying pan. Once rings are hot, spoon ⅓ cup batter into each ring. Cook 4-5 minutes until bubbles pop and batter is mostly cooked. Lift off the rings, turn crumpets over and cook a further 1 minute. Re-grease and reheat the rings and frying pan before cooking the next batch of crumpets. Serve Crumpets while still warm, spread generously with butter and jam  (see Tip)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["8 oz whole milk","9 oz bread flour","1 tbsp active dry yeast","1 tsp salt","1 tsp sugar","8 oz water","½ tsp baking soda","vegetable oil, to grease and fry","unsalted butter, to serve","jam, to serve"]}],"id":"r462676","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-QQ_fCcov9N4\/XZQueSrMl8I\/AAAAAAAAcTs\/7bA6F1XHMWEoYCuVBIQZ7DBTREWxKr3JACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_0aaSWYq-OHo_1Wph.png","title":"Crumpets","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"21 g","calories":"519 kJ \/ 124 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frying pan, egg rings, large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["If making in advance, re-heat crumpets by toasting lightly on both sides before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 15m","10 portions"]}